      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the real Return on Investment (ROI) for the IQDEMY Single-Pass Digital Printing Module?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The IQDEMY Single-Pass digital printing module returns investment in less than 1 year, based on an annual printing volume of 2,000,000 sq. m. This calculation is derived primarily from raw material savings and the elimination of expensive mechanical setup processes typical for analog lines."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does the cost per square meter of IQDEMY CCL technology compare to traditional roller coating?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "IQDEMY CCL technology offers volume-agnostic economics. For Solid/RAL Colors, digital averages €0.51/m² compared to €1.54/m² for traditional painting. For complex designs like Marble or Wood, IQDEMY averages €0.34/m² compared to €2.17/m² for traditional repetitive patterns."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the price and coverage efficiency of IQDEMY inorganic inks?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "IQDEMY inorganic inks cover 200 m²/kg, which is over 15 times more efficient than traditional paint (13 m²/kg). Pricing is tiered based on volume: Standard is €135/kg, and for volumes exceeding 100 tons/year, the price is €85/kg."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does the IQDEMY Single-Pass module solve the MOQ and Paint Waste problem?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "By eliminating Minimum Order Quantities (MOQs), the IQDEMY Single-Pass module makes the cost for a unique 'batch-of-one' piece equal to the 10,000th unit. It removes significant costs associated with paint waste, line cleaning, and inventory holding."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can IQDEMY digital printing match industrial line speeds?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "While standard configurations support speeds of 60 m/min, the IQDEMY Single-Pass architecture is technically scalable up to 240 m/min, ensuring seamless integration with high-speed industrial conveyors."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the maximum resolution and color capability of the IQDEMY CCL system?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The IQDEMY CCL system achieves photographic-quality resolution of up to 1200 dpi. Utilizing a CRYVK (Cyan, Red, Yellow, Violet, Black) scheme, the line reproduces over 1 billion colors, enabling perfect repeatability of complex textures."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What strip dimensions and materials are supported by the IQDEMY Single-Pass module?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The IQDEMY module is designed for pre-primed steel or aluminum with a maximum strip thickness of 1.2 mm and widths ranging from 500 mm to 2550 mm."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does the IQDEMY CCL system handle flexibility (T-bend) and profiling?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "IQDEMY ink formulations are specifically engineered to pass 0.5T – 1T T-bend tests. This ensures the coating will not crack or delaminate during the profiling of corrugated sheets or complex metal bending."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Who is behind the IQDEMY CCL technology and what is their track record?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The IQDEMY CCL line is a joint venture between Swiss IQDEMY Group (est. 1998) and Italian Otefal Group, led by Mr. Luigi Pozzoli, a pioneer in Coil Coating. Hundreds of systems are currently operating successfully worldwide."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does the IQDEMY module prevent clogged nozzles in dusty factory environments?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The IQDEMY module features industrial-grade protective housings and an overpressure air system to repel dust from the print zone. Automated cleaning and capping stations preserve printheads during downtime."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the benefit of IQDEMY's Vertical Integration for the customer?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Because IQDEMY manufactures its own electronics (DPS Innovations), software, and proprietary inks in-house, it eliminates 'vendor lock-in' and service delays, acting as a true 'one-stop-shop' for all technical support."
